body:
`buildah push imagename oci-arichive:zzz.tar` produces a tar file. The tar file contans a blobs/sha256 directory. One of the files in that directory has the content
```json
{
  "schemaVersion":2,
  "config":{
    "mediaType":"application/vnd.oci.image.config.v1+json", 
    "digest":"sha256:68558a5fe468cfc20b609e3bbb0ab4a93570fb193efe0f66b0672c2c8efe3181",
    "size":1120
  },
  "layers":[{
    "mediaType":"application/vnd.oci.image.layer.v1.tar+gzip",
    "digest":"sha256:478ae127a53387d119b5d2c1f64f05ee3d1693efc2ea7bc2b68fd7f68f2b2233",
    "size":40198040
  }]
}
```

The blobs/sha256/478ae127a53387d119b5d2c1f64f05ee3d1693efc2ea7bc2b68fd7f68f2b2233 file is in .tar.gz format.

• Add support for the other [valid layer formats](https://github.com/opencontainers/image-spec/blob/master/layer.md): `application/vnd.oci.image.layer.v1.tar` and `application/vnd.oci.image.layer.v1.tar+zstd` per command line option.

Exporting the image as uncompressed blob has the advantage, that the resulting tar file can be compressed e.g. by xz, which is better than gz and moreover, compressing it only with xz is better than first gz compressing and then compressing the result with xz.

Likewise for the `buildah push oci:.` export
